Name: Isabel Martinez
Artist Statement: Isabel Martinez is an actor and storyteller rooted in community-based work. With a background in devised theatre and a passion for intergenerational healing, her performances explore identity, resilience, and cultural memory. She believes in the power of storytelling to transform both audience and artist, and is especially drawn to collaborative projects that bridge languages, traditions, and borders.
Current Work: Working on a play with women from the Amazon.
Story Excerpt: A memory passed down through water and time.
